glossary.p:
APCs: antigen-presenting cells; AS01: adjuvant system 01; BCG: Bacillus Calmette-Guérin; BCR: B-cell receptor; BLS: Brucella lumazine synthase; BMDCs: bone marrow-derived dendritic cells; CBLB502: BP1569: Entolimod, recombinant flagellin; Bordetella pertussis 1596; CCH: Concholepas concholepas hemocyanin; CCR7: C-C chemokine receptor 7; CEA: carcinoembryonic antigen; cGMP: current good manufacturing practice; CLRs: C-type lectin receptors; COVID-19: coronavirus disease 2019; CRDs: carbohydrate recognition domains; CT: cholera toxin; CXCL: C-X-C motif chemokine ligand; DAMPs: damage-associated molecular patterns; CTLDs: C-type lectin-like domains; DCs: dendritic cells; DC-SIGN: DC-specific ICAM-3–grabbing nonintegrin ESAT-6: early secretory antigenic target-6; ERK: extracellular signal-regulated kinase; ETVAX: enterotoxigenic E. coli vaccine; FDA: Food and Drug Administration; FLH: Fissurella latimarginata hemocyanin; FomA: Porin A from Fusobacterium nucleatum; FU: functional unit; GD1a: disialoganglioside 1a; GM1: monosialotetrahexosyl ganglioside; Gsα: α-subunit of protein G; HAI: hemagglutination inhibition; HBHA: heparin-binding hemagglutinin adhesin; HEK cells: human embryonic kidney cells; HlH: Helix lucorum hemocyanin; HtH: Haliotis tuberculata hemocyanin; HMGB1: high-mobility group box 1; HSP70L1: heat-shock-70-like protein 1; KLH: keyhole limpet hemocyanin; LPS: lipopolysaccharide; LT: heat-labile enterotoxin; M2e: ectodomain matrix 2 protein of influenza virus; MAL: MyD88-adaptor-like; MAPK: mitogen-activated protein kinase; MD-2: myeloid differentiation protein-2; MGL: macrophage galactose lectin; MHC: major histocompatibility complex; migDCs: migratory dendritic cells; ML-I: mistletoe lectin 1; MOMP: major outer membrane protein; MPLA: monophosphoryl lipid A; MR: mannose receptor; MUC1: mucin 1, cell surface associated; MyD88: myeloid differentiation primary response 88; NF-κB: nuclear factor-κB; NOD2: nucleotide-binding oligomerization domain-containing 2; OMPs: outer-membrane proteins; OVA: ovalbumin;
PAPMs: pathogen-associated molecular patterns; PBAs: protein-based adjuvants; PEMs: peritoneal exudate macrophages; PKB: protein kinase B; PI3K-AKT: phosphatidylinositol-3-kinase and protein kinase B; Ply: pneumolysin; PRRs: pattern recognition receptors; QS21: saponin from Quillaja Saponaria; rBCSP31: recombinant Brucella cell-surface protein 31; rCTB: recombinant cholera toxin B subunit; RIG-I: retinoic acid-inducible gene-I-like receptors; RPLL: ribosomal protein L7 L12;
Rpf E: resuscitation-promoting factor E; rPepO: recombinant endopeptidase O; RtH: Rapana thomasiana hemocyanin; SARS-CoV-2: severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2; SBA: soybean agglutinin; SIP: Surface Immunogenic Protein; TB: tuberculosis; TCR: T-cell receptor; Th: T-helper lymphocyte; TGF-β:
transforming growth factor-β;
TIR: Toll/interleukin-1 receptor; TIRAP: TIR domain-containing adaptor protein; TIV: trivalent inactivated influenza vaccine; TLRs: Toll-like receptors; TRAM: TRIF-related adaptor molecule; Treg: regulatory T-cells; TRIF: TIR domain-containing adapter-inducing IFNβ; VAX: a vaccine or vaccination; VPLs: virus-like particles; and WHO: the World Health Organization.
